---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Flora Support"
  description="Support information for Flora Endless Word Search by HSL Innovations."
>
  <section class="page-hero container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Support</p>
    <h1>Flora Endless Word Search</h1>
    <p>
      Need help with Flora? Find gameplay guidance, troubleshooting tips,
      privacy information, accessibility documentation, and ways to share feedback.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card">
    <img
      src="/icons/flora.png"
      alt="Flora Endless Word Search app icon"
      width="96"
      height="96"
      class="app-icon"
    />

    <h2>Getting Started</h2>
    <p>
      Flora Endless Word Search is a relaxing word search game for iPhone and
      iPad. Start a new puzzle, find the hidden words, and complete the full word
      list to finish the puzzle.
    </p>

    <h2>How to Play</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Tap <strong>New Puzzle</strong> from the Home screen.</li>
      <li>Find a word hidden in the letter grid.</li>
      <li>Tap the first letter of the word.</li>
      <li>Tap the last letter of the word.</li>
      <li>Words must be selected in a straight line.</li>
      <li>Words can be found forward or backward.</li>
      <li>Find every word to complete the puzzle automatically.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Stats and Progress</h2>
    <p>
      Flora tracks completed puzzles, words found, current streak, best streak,
      and the date you started playing. In the current version, this information
      is stored locally on your device.
    </p>

    <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        If a word is not accepted, make sure your selection is a straight line
        and matches one of the words in the current puzzle list.
      </li>
      <li>
        If you tap the same letter twice, the current selection is cleared so
        you can try again.
      </li>
      <li>
        If text appears crowded, try rotating your iPad or adjusting your system
        text size in iOS or iPadOS Settings.
      </li>
      <li>
        Haptic feedback may only be noticeable on supported Apple devices.
        Devices without haptic hardware will continue to work normally.
      </li>
      <li>
        If the app behaves unexpectedly, close and reopen the app.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <h3>Why wasn't my word accepted?</h3>
    <p>
      Make sure your selection forms a straight line and matches one of the
      words shown in the current puzzle's word list. Words may also be found in
      reverse.
    </p>

    <h3>Can I save a puzzle and finish it later?</h3>
    <p>
      Not yet. Save and resume functionality is planned for a future update.
    </p>

    <h3>Does Flora require an internet connection?</h3>
    <p>
      No. The current version of Flora works completely offline.
    </p>

    <h3>Can I sync my progress between devices?</h3>
    <p>
      Not in the current version. Future releases may support iCloud sync and
      other Apple account features.
    </p>

    <h3>Will more puzzle categories be added?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes. Flora is designed to grow over time with additional categories,
      gameplay improvements, and quality-of-life features.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy and Accessibility</h2>
    <p>
      Flora is designed with privacy and accessibility in mind. You can review
      the related documentation below.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><a href="/privacy/flora">Flora Privacy Policy</a></li>
      <li><a href="/accessibility/flora">Flora Accessibility Information</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Feedback and Bug Reports</h2>
    <p>
      If you need help, want to report a bug, or have feedback about Flora,
      please contact HSL Innovations through the <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>.
      Please include your device model, iOS or iPadOS version, and the steps that
      led to the issue if you are reporting a bug.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
